  "prompt": "Why do we fall out of love?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why people may fall out of love:\n\n1. Loss of emotional intimacy\n- Communication breakdown\n- Growing apart\n- Lack of shared experiences\n\n2. Unresolved conflicts\n- Frequent arguments\n- Unaddressed resentments\n- Inability to compromise\n\n3. Personal changes\n- Individual growth and evolving goals\n- Different life trajectories\n- Shifting personal values\n\n4. Decreased physical and emotional attraction\n- Routine and predictability\n- Lack of excitement\n- Reduced physical intimacy\n\n5. External stressors\n- Financial pressures\n- Work-related stress\n- Family or health challenges\n\n6. Lack of effort\n- Taking partner for granted\n- Stopping romantic gestures\n- Neglecting relationship maintenance\n\n7. Compatibility issues\n- Fundamental differences\n- Misaligned expectations\n- Incompatible life goals\n\n8. Psychological factors\n- Loss of trust\n- Infidelity\n- Unresolved past traumas\n\n9. Natural relationship cycles\n- Hormonal changes\n- Transitioning from passionate to companionate love\n- Normalization of initial excitement\n\nFalling out of love is complex and often involves multiple interconnected factors. Each relationship is unique, and reasons can vary significantly between individuals.",
